We are currently working on improving our REST API and we need to implement the optional &#x27;fields&#x27; parameter for some actions. Therefore, we would like it to recognize the pattern of the request in the same manner Facebook is currently doing:<p>GET https://graph.facebook.com/me?fields=name,birthday,photos.limit(10).fields(id, picture)<p>After some google searches, we didn&#x27;t find anything.
So far, we came to this (incomplete) solution:<p>(?<expr>(?&term)(?:[,](?&term))<i>){0}
(?<term>(?&value)(?:[.](?&mod))</i>){0}
(?<mod>(limit|fields)\((?&expr)\)){0}
(?<value>\w*){0}
^(?&expr)$<p>The semantic and syntax used is PCRE with the modifier x (PCRE_EXTENDED)<p>Completely different solutions are also more than welcome.<p>Thanks in advance.
